		<h4>UX Recommendations</h4>
		<p>Based on the audit and competitive + usability research, I compiled a "Top UX Recommendations" list that I would integrate into my sketches and prototypes. This list I shared with Product so that they would understand the thought and research behind some of the recommendations and decisions that I would eventually make from the design side.</p>
		<h5>Recommendations</h5>
		<ul>
			<li>Context gives the user confidence to buy. Bigger product images, more product images, and more product information helps users make more informed decisions.</li>
			<li>For products with multiple sizes, like rugs, expose all size options so users have the ability to easily compare and select sizes (versus cramming all into a dropdown).</li>
			<li>Progressive disclosure with product information: on first paint, show critical information, such as name, price, estimated arrival, and delivery date. (Ideally show critical information on a category basis.) Only show other information when user invokes it.</li>
		</ul>
	</div>
</div>

