<div class="text-block row">
	<div class="large-8 columns large-offset-2">
		<h5>Error Classification</h5><br>
		<p><i>1. Severe Errors</i><br>Errors that prevent us from completing transaction and shipping to the customer. The desired error handling behavior is to detect error on key press and interrupt user with error dialog.</p>
		<h5 class="hsmall">Examples:</h5><p>
			<ul>
				<li>Enters a PO box, APO/FPO for shipping</li>
				<li>Enters a non-accepted payment method</li>
				<li>Enters a zip code subject to zone exclusion</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
		<p><i>2. Obvious Errors</i><br>The desired error handling behavior is to detect error on blur and mark field red.</p>
		<h5 class="hsmall">Examples:</h5><p>
			<ul>
				<li>Zip code must be 5 or 9 digits</li>
				<li>Phone number must be 10 digits</li>
				<li>CVC must be 3 or 4 digits (depending on CC type)</li>
				<li>Credit card must be 16 digits</li>
				<li>City and state must be valid</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
		<p><i>3. Non-obvious Errors</i><br>The desired error handling behavior is to detect error when user submits form, show error dialog, and mark erroneous fields red.</p>
		<h5 class="hsmall">Examples:</h5><p>
			<ul>
				<li>Gift card or discount codes invalid</li>
				<li>Fields left empty</li>
				<li>Payment method could not be validated</li>
			</ul>
		</p>
	</div>
</div>

